    <text>
        <body>
        	<div1 type="letter">
        		<pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0339"/>
        		<head>Jim to Mademoiselle Marcelle Guerin <date value="1916-05-30">May 30th 1916</date></head>
        		
        		<opener>
            <dateline><date value="1916-05-30">May 30th 1916</date></dateline>
            
            <salute>Dear Marcelle:</salute>
        		</opener>
        		
        		<p>
            Your very 
            sweet letter of the 
            26th has given me
            a great deal of pleasure.
            I am glad to know in
            a way that you would
            be concerned should I
            be wounded.  Your concern
            makes me feel better &mdash;
            less lonely I might say.
            I have read and re read
            the letter and I cannot
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0341" n="[p.2]"/>
            
            thank you too much
            for what you say.
            Its awfully good of you
            and I’m sure that no
            matter how badly wounded
            I might be your interest
            would help to cure me right
            away.
            </p><p>
            I was already to leave
            yesterday but the clouds
            were too low and it
            rained.  To day the
            clouds are very low
            but I am going to
                        
            <pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0340" n="[p.3]"/>
            
            try and get away
            late this afternoon if
            possible.  I will only go
            as far as Toul which
            I can make in less than
            an hour.  Lieut. De Laage
            flew down from Bar le Duc
            the other day and through
            him I received news of 
            the boys.  Its fierce to
            be held up here while
            they are doing such
            splendid work at Verdun.
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000001107_0342" n="[p.4]"/>
            
            You must tell me about
            the moving pictures when I
            see you.  I’d like so much
            to see them myself.  Could
            you pick out my machine?
            “Mac” was painted on the 
            side.
            </p><p>
            Bill Thaw is chez lui, I
            understand.  Please give him
            my best and say I’ll write 
            soon.
            </p>
        		
        		<closer>
            <salute>Affectionately</salute>
            
            <signed>Jim</signed>
            
            <seg type="postscript">
            Escadrille N. 124<lb/>
            Secteur Postal 24
            </seg>
        		</closer>
        		
